and w. Comeback and St. George

Patrick Brown, Dunbar School;
Sam Mosley, Gililland School,
Tempe; and ten others.

educational consultant, said
scholarship gifts are accepted

Keeping fit is the chief way to
avoid injuries during sports.
Here are some easy to do stand
up exercises to try every morn
ing. Raise your arms forward
until parallel with floor; swing
to the sides and back as far as
they will go; return to sides and
repeat ten times. Raise your left
leg forward as high as you can,
keeping knee straight and toes
pointed, lower it, and alternate
with your right leg, repeating
ten times each. Slowly raise and
lower yourself on the toes ten
times.


Special to way-out car model
lovers: The prize-winning Pre-
dicta is the latest real car copied
in 1/2" scale by Monogram Mod
els, Inc. Basically, it's a 1856
Thunderbird, but you wouldn't
know it to look at it. There's the
bubbletop first used by Daryl
Starbird, designer of the orig
inal, Unistick steering and dual
controls so the car can be oper-
ated from either the right or left
seat. The hood opens and closes
and the front wheels can be
steered. Power comes from a '57
Chrysler engine with fuel injec-
ton.
